First line says that we want to build 'kilo' and 'Kilo.c' is required to build it.

Second line specifies the command to run.
( ensure second line is tabbed, now whitespace )

Explaining arguments

gcc :- Variable that makes 'make' use 'gcc' by default

-Wall :- All warning - get compiler to warn you when code may be wrong

-Wextra :- turn on even more warnings 

-pendantic :- turn of even more warnings

-std=c99 :- Specifies exact version of C standard we're uring
( can declare vars anywhere within a function, instead of just at top of function )

